fields.name: Chicken
fields.description: Poultry builds lean muscle mass in dogs and delivers Omega 6 fatty acids that help sustain healthy skin and shiny coats. It’s also a great source of essential amino acids and glucosamine, which helps promote bone health.

fields.name: Beef
fields.description: Rich in essential amino acids, minerals and vitamins, lean beef is also an excellent diet food for pets.

fields.name: Salmon
fields.description: Supports the immune system and can be beneficial for skin and coat health. There has also been some indication that it may benefit dogs with allergies.

fields.name: Lamb
fields.description: Lamb is an excellent source of high-quality protein and essential amino acids, which are vital nutrients for your dog.

fields.name: Brown Rice
fields.description: Recommended for a healthy diet because it contains extra nutrients. Brown rice tends to be a bit more caloric, but it also contains extra protein and fiber that offer these health benefits: Lowers cholesterol. Controls blood sugar levels.

fields.name: Rolled Oats
fields.description: Rich in Antioxidants, Including Avenanthramides, Rolled Oats Contain a Powerful Soluble Fiber Called Beta-Glucan and Can Lower Cholesterol Levels and Protect LDL Cholesterol From Damage

fields.name: Quinoa
fields.description: Quinoa contains the Plant Compounds Quercetin and Kaempferol, is Gluten Free, and is Very High in Fiber and Protein, Much Higher Than Most Grains, With All the Essential Amino Acids.

fields.name: Sweet Potatoes
fields.description: Sweet potatoes are low in calories and higher in beta-carotene and vitamin C, vitamin B, potassium and manganese. A great filler for any treat.

fields.name: Blueberries
fields.description: Blueberries are Low in Calories But High in Nutrients, and full of Antioxidants.

fields.name: Pumpkin
fields.description: Pumpkin is Nutrient-Rich, Benefits the Eyes, helps to Boost Immune Health and Moisturizes your pet's Skin & Coat.

fields.name: Spinach
fields.description: Spinach contains large amounts of vitamins A, B, C, and K. It also contains iron, antioxidants, beta-carotene, and roughage, which stimulate the digestive tract.

fields.name: Green Beans
fields.description: Green beans are full of important vitamins and minerals, such as protein, iron, calcium, and vitamins B6, A, C, and K. Green beans are also full of fiber and are low in calories, which can help dogs feel full when they are dieting

fields.name: Apples
fields.description: Apples are a healthy, and low calorie treat. They are a good source of vitamin A, vitamin C, and dietary fiber, and they also help keep a dog's teeth clean along with freshening the breath.

fields.name: Cantaloupe
fields.description: Cantaloupes are loaded vitamin A and lots of beta carotene, which helps reduce the risk of cancer and prevents cell damage. Also a good source of vitamins B-6 and C, fiber, folate, niacin and potassium.

fields.name: Peanut Butter
fields.description: Peanut Butter adds Vitamin E, and Vitamin B which are very important for a shiny, healthy skin and coat. It is also a good source of fats and protein.

fields.name: Bone Meal
fields.description: Bone meal contains many nutrient minerals, including phosphorous, which can help your dog's body to better absorb other nutrients and aid digestion. Bone meal can help soothe difficult digestion in dogs with flatulence and diarrhea

fields.name: Eggs
fields.description: Eggs are a great source of very digestible protein, riboflavin, and selenium. For some dogs that are prone to digestive upset, eggs can give them a little protein boost.

fields.name: Liver
fields.description: Liver Is Rich In Vitamin A, is a High Source Of Omega 3 And Omega 6 Fatty Acids, Iron, Copper and Niacin.
